## Dark mode design principles

The primary objective of dark mode is accessibility, particularly for people with light sensitivity (photophobia). Designed for use in low-light environments, we reduce the brightness, contrast, and vibrancy of the UI while maintaining accessible contrast ratios. This approach also helps minimise eye strain, visual fatigue, and headaches.

\
